Printing Univariate Outlier Detection Results

Source: R/print.uniOutliers.R
print.uniOutliers.Rd

Prints identified univariate outliers using the specified method (boxplot, MAD, or Grubbs' test).

Usage

# S3 method for class 'uniOutliers'
print(x, ...)

Arguments

x

The results from a univariate outlier detection function (e.g., output from uniOutliers).

...

not used

Value

A formatted print of the outlier results, including the detected outliers, their row numbers, and the method used.

Examples

object <- uniOutliers(data = mtcars, x = "wt", method = "mad")
print(object)
#> 
#> ── Method Chosen: mad ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#> Variable: wt
#> ✔ No outliers detected.

object2 <- uniOutliers(data = mtcars, x = "wt", method = "boxplot")
print(object2)
#> 
#> ── Method Chosen: boxplot ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#> Variable: wt
#> 
#> Outliers Detected for:
#> 
#> 
#>  Row Number    Outlier Value 
#> ------------  ---------------
#>      16            5.424     
#>      17            5.345     

object3 <- uniOutliers(data = mtcars, x = "wt", method = "grubbs")
print(object3)
#> 
#> ── Method Chosen: grubbs ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#> Variable: wt
#> ✔ No outliers detected.
